    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your<strong> orzo pasta</strong> to a pot of plenty of<strong> boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, cook for 6-8 min or until cooked with a slight bite, then drain and rinse under <strong>cold running water </strong>until cooled</p><p>Drain the orzo thoroughly, then return it to the pot with a small drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and a squeeze of<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><strong>lemon juice</strong> and mix it all up</p>",
